doc.after: The origins of Twelfth Air Force are traced back to a series of mid 1942 Allied planners meetings to develop a strategy for the North African invasion or Operation TORCH Because this extensive operation required a new organization to provide enough manpower and equipment activation plans were prepared simultaneously with the invasion strategy
